    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Appendix - DS10</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Reference material specific to the DS10 platform -- the only model EmulatR currently models and drives end to end. This page summarizes the hardware EmulatR presents and the device manifest that defines it; the sub-topics carry the environment-variable reference, the SRM and SuperIO analysis, and the engineering status.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Hardware summary</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The AlphaServer DS10 is a single-processor Tsunami-family workstation. EmulatR presents a single 21264 (EV6) CPU, the 21272 (Tsunami) core-logic chipset, and a Cypress CY82C693 combination ISA bridge / IDE controller / SuperIO. The default configuration reports 1024 MB of memory and a 268 MHz cycle clock. The platform is defined declaratively by <text styleclass="Code Example">ds10_platform.json</text>; a missing manifest is a hard startup error with no fallback.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">PCI device manifest</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">All devices sit on hose 0, bus 0. From <text styleclass="Code Example">ds10_platform.json</text>:</para>
