    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The IDE controller carries two storage units on its primary channel: <text styleclass="Code Example">dqa0</text> (primary master) is the bootable ATA fixed disk (raw flat image, 512-byte sectors, byte offset = LBA x 512), and <text styleclass="Code Example">dqa1</text> (primary slave) is the ATAPI CD. Media for each is resolved from the manifest against the <text styleclass="Code Example">[Storage] diskDir</text> in the ini; an empty media string means no disk / no disc.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">IIC / FRU devices</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal">The DS10 manifest also models the IIC (I2C) bus the firmware probes during GCT/FRU initialization: two system-status devices (0x70, 0x72), an SMB FRU EEPROM for the DS10 board (0xA2) and one for the EV6 CPU (0xA4), and a 256-byte RCM NVRAM (0xC0). The PCI vendor/device IDs and BAR sizes are marked provisional in the manifest pending a real hardware dump.</para>
